 {"id":"frankenjax-vzo","title":"UBS: classify test-only panic/assert inventory","description":"Follow-up from frankenjax-gn6. UBS baseline on 2026-04-27 reports 115 Rust panic! criticals and 3,727 assert macro warnings, but the sampled hits are predominantly #[cfg(test)] modules and integration tests (for example fj-api/src/lib.rs test assertions, fj-core/fj-interpreters test-log wrappers, fj-conformance tests). Triage these into test-only acceptable-failure patterns vs production panic surfaces, then either refactor noisy test helpers or document/suppress the test-only class so future UBS gates do not obscure production issues.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-27T05:48:12.379180518Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-28T00:19:43.319970704Z","closed_at":"2026-04-28T00:19:43.318177801Z","close_reason":"Complete: all 52 panic! and 2,925 unwrap/expect are test-only. Zero production panic surfaces. Report at artifacts/ubs_classification_report.md","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenjax-wrj","title":"Remove residual stub/placeholder wording from tests, logs, and comments","description":"CONTEXT: After closing the runtime placeholder/stub issues, a repo text audit still finds residual wording in non-runtime surfaces. These are not behavior bugs but they keep the placeholder/stub epic open and muddy the project state.\\n\\nCHANGES REQUIRED:\\n  1. In crates/fj-conformance/tests/control_flow_conformance.rs, remove the  wording from the Switch dispatch fallback log while preserving the documented dispatch gap.\\n  2. In crates/fj-trace/src/lib.rs, rename the  test and its fixture id string so they no longer use .\\n  3. In crates/fj-lax/src/lib.rs, rename , its JSON/log labels, and artifact filenames so they describe implemented special-function rejection coverage without .\\n  4. In crates/fj-lax/src/tensor_ops.rs, replace the inline  comment in reshape inference with accurate wording describing a temporary inferred-axis slot.\\n\\nTESTING:\\n  - cargo test -p fj-trace <renamed test filter if needed>\\n  - cargo test -p fj-lax <affected tests or full crate if simpler>\\n  - cargo test -p fj-conformance control_flow_conformance if touched path is exercised there\\n  - workspace check/clippy/fmt per AGENTS.md, via rch for cargo commands\\n\\nACCEPTANCE:\\n  - No residual , , or  wording remains in those touched surfaces.\\n  - Tests continue to pass and artifact/log names stay coherent.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-03T02:44:11.239637820Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T02:49:19.161344309Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T02:49:19.161036606Z","close_reason":"Removed residual placeholder/stub wording from trace/lax/conformance test surfaces and comments; verified with targeted rch tests plus workspace check/clippy/fmt","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenjax-ws4","title":"Clean fj-ad test panic and unwrap inventory","description":"UBS on crates/fj-ad/src/lib.rs still exits 1 after frankenjax-x8f because of pre-existing test-only panic/unwrap inventory: 36 panic! macros and 1,577 unwrap/expect hits under cfg(test), plus broader assertion/test-helper warnings. Production code before cfg(test) is clean for unwrap/expect/panic after x8f. Convert test panic arms and lock unwraps to explicit Result/panic_any-style helpers in a separate focused cleanup.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-27T06:52:36.415988525Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T07:09:32.376440405Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T07:09:32.374470223Z","close_reason":"Completed fj-ad test panic cleanup","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
